$interpreted: Yan-Bo: Joined the resistance, your royal friend did. Attempted to overthrow the Alliance's corrupted system, he tried.
Yan-Bo: Royal bodyguard you were, hesitating to choose sides. In the end. your friend died, he did. Within the Alliance, Tigers lost power and prestige...
Pang: Yao accused me as the traitor before his own untimely death. I was exiled from the East Alliance, also because of Yao.
Pang: That's how I became a lone ranger, not willing to let myself feel strongly for others anymore...
Yan-Bo: Looking for something, anything to do, you are. Desire you express to learn from me. Pass time as an excuse, forgetting your painful experience.
Yan-Bo: All bark but no bite. Sensitive you are, surprised I am.
Pang: You simply don't understand! The dignity of my tribe, a lifelong friendship I once had...
Pang: Caught between a rock and a hard place, can you relate to that at all?
Yan-Bo: Deep breath. Fruits I plucked, have some.
Pang: Hmm, rather juicy.
Yan-Bo: Not bad huh? A few more, take some bites.
Pang: Phooey, ugh...what's that foul taste?
Yan-Bo: Ha ha ha. On the rotten parts you've bitten down.
Pang: You gave me a pest infested fruit? Ack ack...
Yan-Bo: Some wine you drink here, wash out unpleasant sensation it will.
Yan-Bo: Hmm. No dilemma I see you. Both side take into account, too kind you were.
Yan-Bo: Figuring out how nobody gets hurt, that you tried.
Pang: ...Perhaps...
Yan-Bo: Pest bit small part only, like this fruit. Once the rotten flesh is removed, edible is the rest.
Yan-Bo: Dilly dally you do, eventually rotting the fruit. Come to the point of no return, all things will.
Pang: You mean to say?
Pang: Why am I...what have you given me to drink?
Yan-Bo: Do. Or do not. There is no try. Pang of guilt, you are no longer.
Pang: Err...where am I? Where is everyone else?
Pang: Oh right. Yao mentioned slaying the Alliance's higher ups, so common folk may have a better life.
Pang: What, what should I do...
Conscience: Need you even ask? Help Yao of course!
Conscience: The higher ups will stop at nothing for their personal gain, even at the expense of others. Are you really that oblivious?
Pang: I am aware, but must we resort to such extremes?
Conscience: We are the same inside. We should trust Yao, and strive for a better future together!
Pang: No, I cannot let Yao do this anymore. I must stop him!
Pang: YOU?!
Conscience: Are you off to catch Yao? Excellent. I am you, you are me.
Conscience: Blood is thicker than water, or so they say. But for the sake of all Tigers, we must uphold principles of righteousness above family loyalty!
Pang: No...securing the Tigers' power within the Alliance is indeed important. But that will not be the reason as to why I must stop Yao!
Conscience: Have you no concern for the consequences? What if the Alliance receives word that Tiger royalty has joined the resistance?
Conscience: You have no right to serve the Tigers!
Pang: I must stop tragedy before it unfolds. No regrets...
Pang: Where's Yao? MUST. STOP. HIM...
Pang: Was it all a dream?
Yan-Bo: Within your dream, an answer you seem have found.
Puggi: ——Knick nack paddy wack, Pang!
Puggi: Hestia's at it with the frogodiles again!
Yan-Bo: And now, you know what to do.
